DEC 11
Flyer Content (Carousel — 5 slides):

Cover: 5 Beginner Mistakes in Tech Learning
Slide 1: Trying to Learn Everything at Once
Beginners often attempt to master too many languages, frameworks, or tools simultaneously, leading to confusion and burnout. Focus on one technology at a time.
Slide 2: Skipping the Fundamentals
Many skip core concepts (like algorithms, data structures, or basic syntax) and jump straight to advanced topics or frameworks, resulting in weak foundational knowledge.
Slide 3: Not Practicing Enough
Reading or watching tutorials without hands-on coding leads to poor retention. Consistent practice and building small projects are essential for real understanding.
Slide 4: Avoiding Debugging and Problem-Solving
Beginners may copy-paste code without understanding errors or debugging. Learning to troubleshoot and read error messages is crucial for growth.
Slide 5: Neglecting Documentation and Community Resources
Many ignore official documentation, forums, or community Q&A, missing out on valuable learning and support. Learning to read docs and ask good questions is a key skill.


